ICN Pharmaceuticals Inc saidit purchased the remaining 225,000 shares of Viratek Inc&lt;VIRA.O> owned by Eastman Kodak Co owned as part of apreviously announced program.    The company said it paid Kodak 10.50 dlrs a share or 2.4mln dlrs. As previously announced, ICN also said it authorizedthe additional purchase of up to 1.5 mln shares of Viratekcommon. To date, ICN said it bought a total of about 1.2 mlnshares of Viratek, including the shares purchased from Kodak.    The company said it now owns 56 pct of Viratek as a resultof these transactions. Reuter&#3;